
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the [stream] argument is true and, if so, inserts nodes before the first [fork] node within the current context. It then evaluates the [invoke] node within a new [fork], allowing parallel execution of the [invoke] lambda object. The [insert-before] slot is used to modify the node structure dynamically, while [fork] enables concurrent execution.
if
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/stream
   .lambda
      insert-before:x:./*/fork/0
         get-nodes:x:@.invoke
      fork
         eval:x:@.invoke
